The paper deals with a signal processing problem of extracting a sequence of functions from their convolutions, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), signal processing (cs.SI), and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses an application in wireless communications, which further supports the relevance to cs.IT and cs.SI.
